The African National Congress Women’s League (ANCWL) members of Ike Maphoto branch in Polokwane spiced up a business breakfast this morning (Friday) with a programme that included messages of empowerment as well as a fiery speech by former ruling party Provincial Chairperson and Small Business Development Deputy Minister Cassel Mathale.
The meeting took place less than a week before Wednesday’s elections and ahead of a 5 km walk and 10 km fun run to be hosted by the branch tomorrow morning and a gala dinner to fundraise for election work by the party in the province tonight.
Story and photo: YOLANDE NEL
